t Humanities significantly engages, provokes, and contributes to the dynamic field and inquiry of sound studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSound (Philosophy). 0aSoundsxPolitical aspects. 0aSoundsxPsychological aspects. 0aSoundsxSociological aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z978311062111240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096040440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520960404423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520960404/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles